<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-314-346  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 314 346.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Modern Office Technology  April 1990 v35 n4 p38(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>File tracking.(part of a special section on records management)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Records management (RM) software should be considered as analternative to manual systems when volume exceeds workable limits,manual recordkeeping becomes too cumbersome and preparation ofsummary reports becomes too costly.andP;  The three basic types ofrecords management software include programs developed in-house,off-the-shelf databases that can be tailored to individual needs,and ready-to-run packages.andP;  Major benefits of RM software includesemiautomatic checking of records in and out of file, a means offollowing up overdue files, and reduction of the possibility oflost files.andP;  Items to be considered when selecting an RM packageinclude the experience and ranking of the vendor, theuser-friendliness of the package, completeness of userdocumentation, security provisions, speed and response time,interfaces with other hardware and software, and the level oftraining and support supplied by the vendor.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Records ManagementSoftware SelectionOffice AutomationGuidelines.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Factors to consider when choosing a computerized recordsmanagement system. (table)Vendors of barcode, document management software. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>